# List of _Keeping Up with the Kardashians_ episodes

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia

Jump to navigation Jump to search

_[Keeping Up with the Kardashians](/wiki/Keeping_Up_with_the_Kardashians
"Keeping Up with the Kardashians")_ is an American reality television series.
Its premise was originated with [Ryan Seacrest](/wiki/Ryan_Seacrest "Ryan
Seacrest"), who additionally serves as an [executive
producer](/wiki/Executive_producer "Executive producer"). The series focuses
on sisters [Kourtney](/wiki/Kourtney_Kardashian "Kourtney Kardashian"),
[Kim](/wiki/Kimberly_Kardashian "Kimberly Kardashian"), and [Khloé
Kardashian](/wiki/Khlo%C3%A9_Kardashian "Khloé Kardashian").

It additionally places emphasis on their brother [Rob
Kardashian](/wiki/Rob_Kardashian "Rob Kardashian"), their mother [Kris
Jenner](/wiki/Kris_Jenner "Kris Jenner"), their step-parent [Bruce
Jenner](/wiki/Bruce_Jenner "Bruce Jenner") (now known as [Caitlyn
Jenner](/wiki/Caitlyn_Jenner "Caitlyn Jenner")), their half-sisters
[Kendall](/wiki/Kendall_Jenner "Kendall Jenner") and [Kylie
Jenner](/wiki/Kylie_Jenner "Kylie Jenner"), and Kourtney's now ex-boyfriend,
Scott Disick. Khloé's ex-husband [Lamar Odom](/wiki/Lamar_Odom "Lamar Odom")
developed a major position as part of the supporting cast in the fourth
season, though he was not a regular cast member in following seasons, and
rarely appeared in season eight while attempting to fix his marriage with
Khloé.[1] Along in season seven [Kanye West](/wiki/Kanye_West "Kanye West")
became a recurring cast members after dating Kim then marrying her in season
nine. In seasons eight and nine, Caitlyn's children [Brody](/wiki/Brody_Jenner
"Brody Jenner") and [Brandon](/wiki/Brandon_%26_Leah#Brandon_Jenner "Brandon &
Leah"), and Brandon's wife, [Leah](/wiki/Brandon_%26_Leah#Leah_Jenner "Brandon
& Leah") became recurring cast members.

_Keeping Up with the Kardashians_ is often criticized for emphasizing the
"[famous for being famous](/wiki/Famous_for_being_famous "Famous for being
famous")" concept and appearing to fabricate aspects of its storyline. The
series has produced the spin-offs _[Kourtney and Kim Take
Miami](/wiki/Kourtney_and_Kim_Take_Miami "Kourtney and Kim Take Miami")_ ,
_[Kourtney and Kim Take New York](/wiki/Kourtney_and_Kim_Take_New_York
"Kourtney and Kim Take New York")_ , _[Khloé&
Lamar](/wiki/Khlo%C3%A9_%26_Lamar "Khloé & Lamar")_, _[Kourtney and Khloé Take
The Hamptons](/wiki/Kourtney_and_Khlo%C3%A9_Take_The_Hamptons "Kourtney and
Khloé Take The Hamptons")_ , _[Dash Dolls](/wiki/Dash_Dolls "Dash Dolls")_ ,
_[I Am Cait](/wiki/I_Am_Cait "I Am Cait")_ , _[Revenge Body with Khloé
Kardashian](/wiki/Revenge_Body_with_Khlo%C3%A9_Kardashian "Revenge Body with
Khloé Kardashian")_ , _[Rob& Chyna](/wiki/Rob_%26_Chyna "Rob & Chyna")_, and
_[Life of Kylie](/wiki/Life_of_Kylie "Life of Kylie")_.

### Season 1
(2007)[[edit](/w/index.php?title=List_of_Keeping_Up_with_the_Kardashians_episodes&action=edit&section=3
"Edit section: Season 1 \(2007\)")]

No.  
overall| No. in  
season| Title| Original air date  
---|---|---|---  
1| 1| "I'm Watching You"| October 14, 2007 (2007-10-14)  
Bruce and Kris Jenner celebrate their anniversary. Kim And Tommy Davis buys
them a stripper pole as a gift, and the youngest Jenner plays on it. Kim
appears on _[The Tyra Banks Show](/wiki/The_Tyra_Banks_Show "The Tyra Banks
Show")_. Kourtney deals with relationship drama.  
2| 2| "Managing Mom"| October 21, 2007 (2007-10-21)  
Kim and Kris, her manager, argue over the management of Kim's appearances and
schedule. Meanwhile, Kris hires a nanny, [Bree](/wiki/Bree_Olson "Bree
Olson"), who is not as appropriate and nanny-decent as she hoped.  
3| 3| "Brody in the House"| October 28, 2007 (2007-10-28)  
Kourtney, Kim and Khloé go to Mexico for a [Girls Gone
Wild](/wiki/Girls_Gone_Wild_\(franchise\) "Girls Gone Wild \(franchise\)")
photo shoot without telling Bruce, afraid that he would disapprove. When he
finds out, he leaves his son Brody Jenner to look after Kylie and Kendall
while he heads to Mexico to confront them. Unfortunately, leaving Brody with
his daughters creates even more chaos.  
4| 4| "Birthday Suit"| November 4, 2007 (2007-11-04)  
[Playboy](/wiki/Playboy "Playboy") magazine contacts Kris, asking her to tell
Kim that they want her to be on the cover of their December 2007 issue. Kim is
hesitant at first, but Kris encourages her. To show Kris what a difficult
decision it is, Kim proposing trading places and plays Kris' manager and
setting her mom up for a semi-nude shoot. Kim gets the skimpiest outfit she
can. Kris's best picture is her topless, in an American flag towel/blanket.
Kris enjoys the shoot, surprising Kim.  
5| 5| "Remembering Dad"| November 11, 2007 (2007-11-11)  
The family remembers [Robert Kardashian](/wiki/Robert_Kardashian "Robert
Kardashian") on his death anniversary. Khloé, not dealing well with the
anniversary, gets drunk and ends up arrested for a
[DUI](/wiki/Driving_under_the_influence "Driving under the influence").  
6| 6| "You Are So Pregnant Dude"| November 18, 2007 (2007-11-18)  
Kourtney, Kim and Khloé are about to leave for [Las
Vegas](/wiki/Las_Vegas_Valley "Las Vegas Valley") when Kourtney has a
pregnancy scare. Meanwhile, Kendall and Kylie ask their dad for a puppy, which
causes a disagreement between their parents.  
7| 7| "Helping Hand"| November 25, 2007 (2007-11-25)  
Rob gets set up on a date but catches his sisters spying on him. Khloé and
Kourtney find out that a homeless man, Shorty, is living behind their store
[D-A-S-H](/wiki/D-A-S-H "D-A-S-H"), and clean up his appearance.  
8| 8| "The Price of Fame"| December 2, 2007 (2007-12-02)  
Scandalous photos of Kourtney surface, scaring and humiliating Kim, who
already feels like she really messed up with her sex tape.  
  
### Season 2
(2008)[[edit](/w/index.php?title=List_of_Keeping_Up_with_the_Kardashians_episodes&action=edit&section=4
"Edit section: Season 2 \(2008\)")]

No.  
overall| No. in  
season| Title| Original air date  
---|---|---|---  
9| 1| "Kim becomes a Diva"| March 9, 2008 (2008-03-09)  
The family think that Kim is slowly becoming a diva. Kourtney finds shocking
texts in Scott's Blackberry.  
10| 2| "Rob's New Girlfriend"| March 16, 2008 (2008-03-16)  
Rob falls in love with pop star [Adrienne Bailon](/wiki/Adrienne_Bailon
"Adrienne Bailon"), a [Cheetah Girl](/wiki/The_Cheetah_Girls_\(group\) "The
Cheetah Girls \(group\)"), but is left depressed when she leaves for India for
three months to shoot a film. After consulting a nutritionist, Kris decides to
build a chicken coop so the family will have healthier eggs from chickens they
raise themselves.  
11| 3| "Khloé Wants to Act"| March 23, 2008 (2008-03-23)  
Despite Kim's disapproval, Khloé decides to pursue an acting career.
Meanwhile, Bruce receives a fashion makeover.  
12| 4| "Kris the Cheerleader"| March 30, 2008 (2008-03-30)  
Members of the Old School Crew contact Kris: they want her to be a
cheerleader. Kris is worried about auditioning, especially after a knee
injury. Meanwhile, Khloé has a woman-to-woman talk with Kendall, with help
from Kim, Kourtney, and Kylie.  
13| 5| "Khloé's Blind Dates"| April 6, 2008 (2008-04-06)  
Kim and Kourtney, worried about Khloé being single, start an online-dating
profile for her. Khloé gets angry but goes along with the speed dates.
Meanwhile, Bruce teaches Kendall about doing chores and earning her own money
but Kendall hires a handyman and takes the money and the credit for his work.  
14| 6| "Learning Self-Defense"| April 13, 2008 (2008-04-13)  
After [D-A-S-H](/wiki/D-A-S-H "D-A-S-H") is vandalized, Kourtney, Kim and
Khloé take self-defense classes. Rob considers dropping out of
[USC](/wiki/University_of_Southern_California "University of Southern
California") to pursue professional modeling.  
15| 7| "Kardashian Civil War"| April 27, 2008 (2008-04-27)  
Kim battles against Kourtney and Khloé after she purchases a
[Bentley](/wiki/Bentley "Bentley"). Kris gets drunk with a friend and gets a
tattoo. Bruce experiences a mid-life crisis.  
16| 8| "Kardashian Family Vacation"| May 4, 2008 (2008-05-04)  
Bruce thinks a family ski-trip to Colorado will ease some of the family chaos,
but first it intensifies his midlife crisis as he spends time with guys who
are Rob's age. Meanwhile, the family gangs up on Kim, claiming she's not
joining in the family quality time. Kim, feeling hurt, leaves Colorado, but an
apology message from Khloé persuades her to return. The clan enjoys the rest
of their vacation together.  
17| 9| "Kim's Calendar for Reggie"| May 11, 2008 (2008-05-11)  
Kim shoots a sexy calendar for Reggie, but Kris distributes it for public
sale. Kim gets back at her mom by selling the nude poster from Season 1. Bruce
hopes to inspire Kourtney and Khloé, and earn their respect, by taking them to
one of his motivational speeches.  
18| 10| "New Perspective in New Orleans"| May 19, 2008 (2008-05-19)  
When the girls visit New Orleans for a charity pool tournament organized by
Reggie, they meet a family devastated by [Hurricane
Katrina](/wiki/Hurricane_Katrina "Hurricane Katrina"). Meanwhile, Kris' cousin
CiCi crashes Bruce's plans for a romantic weekend.  
19| 11| "Junk in the Trunk"| May 26, 2008 (2008-05-26)  
Kourtney, Kim, Khloé, and Rob share their favorite moments and outtakes from
the series.  
  
### Season 3
(2009)[[edit](/w/index.php?title=List_of_Keeping_Up_with_the_Kardashians_episodes&action=edit&section=5

season| Title| Original air date

20| 1| "Free Khloé"| March 8, 2009 (2009-03-08)  
Kris is furious at Khloé when she goes to jail for violating her probation.
Kris believes her meltdown might have something to do with the upcoming
anniversary of Robert Kardashian's death. Kris talks to her mom about her
feelings and visits her late ex-husband's grave.  
21| 2| "Kourt's First Cover"| March 15, 2009 (2009-03-15)  
Kourtney hires Kris as her manager after [944 Magazine](/wiki/944_Magazine
"944 Magazine") asks her to do a cover shoot. However, Kris does not do well
managing both Kourtney and Kim, who must go to [Comic-
Con](/wiki/San_Diego_Comic-Con_International "San Diego Comic-Con
International") and promote her new film, _[Disaster
Movie](/wiki/Disaster_Movie "Disaster Movie")_. Rob and Adrienne encounter
problems when they move in together.  
22| 3| "I'd Rather Go Naked... Or Shopping"| March 22, 2009 (2009-03-22)  
Khloé faces pressure about her weight when she decides to do [PETA](/wiki/PETA
"PETA")'s "I'd Rather Go Naked Than Wear Fur" campaign. Kris and Kourtney
confront Kim about her shopping addiction.  
23| 4| "Pussycat Vision"| March 29, 2009 (2009-03-29)  
Kim gets [LASIK](/wiki/LASIK "LASIK") eye surgery after struggling to see
herself in a mirror at a dance rehearsal with [Pussycat
Dolls](/wiki/Pussycat_Dolls "Pussycat Dolls") creator [Robin
Antin](/wiki/Robin_Antin "Robin Antin"). Bruce is anxious to talk to Kendall
and Kylie about his [colonoscopy](/wiki/Colonoscopy "Colonoscopy"). Kim
performs with the Pussycat Dolls on the [Las Vegas
Strip](/wiki/Las_Vegas_Strip "Las Vegas Strip").  
24| 5| "All for One and One for Kim"| April 5, 2009 (2009-04-05)  
Kim's perfume line causes friction with Kris, Khloé, and Kourtney. Kris, not
feeling so connected to Bruce anymore, searches for a common interest with
him.  
25| 6| "Cinderella Story"| April 19, 2009 (2009-04-19)  
Khloé gets a [DNA](/wiki/DNA "DNA") test to see if Kris is her real mother,
which upsets Kris. After Rob borrows Kim's car and gets a new tattoo, his
unusual behavior causes concern among the family.  
26| 7| "The Two Year Itch"| April 26, 2009 (2009-04-26)  
Kourtney and Scott get in another argument after she accuses him of cheating
again. Meanwhile, Khloé secretly gets a [biopsy](/wiki/Biopsy "Biopsy") for
skin cancer, which scares Kris after she finds out.  
27| 8| "Distance Makes the Heart Grow Fonder"| May 3, 2009 (2009-05-03)  
Khloé goes to New York to host a fashion show and becomes interested in moving
there to open a second D-A-S-H store. Kim's focus on her career forces her to
choose between it and Reggie.  
28| 9| "Leaving the Nest"| May 10, 2009 (2009-05-10)  
Khloé looks for apartments in New York, which upsets Kris, who does not want
her to leave L.A. Kourtney and Kim get Kris a chimpanzee after she expresses a
desire to have another baby.  
29| 10| "Meet the Kardashians"| May 17, 2009 (2009-05-17)  
The family goes on a camping trip to meet Adrienne's family. Meanwhile, Bruce
undergoes [plastic surgery](/wiki/Plastic_surgery "Plastic surgery") to fix
the mistakes that were made during his treatments in earlier years to fix
injuries that occurred during his sporting career.  
30| 11| "What's Yours is Mine"| May 25, 2009 (2009-05-25)  
Kourtney borrows Kim's personal belongings without her permission. Bruce
struggles with Kylie wearing "grownup" clothes and too much makeup for her
age. Rob breaks up with Adrienne and moves in with Kim.  
31| 12| "Double Trouble"| May 25, 2009 (2009-05-25)  
Khloé's new boyfriend [Rashad McCants](/wiki/Rashad_McCants "Rashad McCants")
cheats on her. Kourtney catches Scott with another girl and starts to think
that Scott may not be the best guy for her.  
  
### Season 4
(2009–10)[[edit](/w/index.php?title=List_of_Keeping_Up_with_the_Kardashians_episodes&action=edit&section=6

No.

season| Title| Original air date  
---|---|---|---  
32| 1| "The Wedding"| November 8, 2009 (2009-11-08)  
Khloé and [Lamar Odom](/wiki/Lamar_Odom "Lamar Odom") get married. Rob
attempts to rekindle his relationship with his ex-girlfriend Adrienne Bailon.
Kim realizes she misses her boyfriend Reggie Bush, and Kourtney and Scott try
to improve their relationship.  
33| 2| "Scott on the Rocks"| December 13, 2009 (2009-12-13)  
Kourtney and Scott find themselves pitted against her family, especially
Khloé, because they disapprove of him.  
34| 3| "Hot Cup of Love"| December 20, 2009 (2009-12-20)  
When Khloé slaps Scott, Kourtney will not talk to her until she takes an
anger-management class. A friend gives Kris a male-enhancement drug and she
tries it on Bruce by slipping it into his coffee but Rob accidentally gets
that coffee cup and lands in the hospital because of what follows.  
35| 4| "Baby Blues"| December 27, 2009 (2009-12-27)  
Khloé gets excited when she thinks she's pregnant, but it turns out that she
is not. When Kim lies to everyone to get out of doing things, Kris and Bruce
get upset, but she may learn a lesson when she lies to Kendall and Kylie.  
36| 5| "Shape Up or Ship Out"| January 3, 2010 (2010-01-03)  
Scott fails to take Kourtney's pregnancy seriously, so she threatens to end
their relationship. Kris upsets Bruce by not letting him buy a helicopter toy
or make any financial decisions. Khloé pays Bruce to do jobs for her. Kris
buys a $4000 dress for 1 event and Kim, Khloé, and Bruce play "scavenger hunt"
by hiding the dress until Kris gives Bruce his ATM card to buy the helicopter
toy. Rob tries to rekindle his relationship with Adrienne after seeing her at
Khloé's wedding, seeming to stalk her by calling her 24/7. When he plans to
visit her in New York, he receives an e-mail from her new boyfriend that
informs him that it's over between them. He's heartbroken but decides to try
to move on.  
37| 6| "Must Love Dogs"| January 10, 2010 (2010-01-10)  
Dog-non-lover Kim finds herself taking in, and loving, a stray Chihuahua until
she must give up "Princess" because of medical problems. Bruce pressures Rob
to move out of the house, and he gets a job developing his own skin-care line
with Kourtney's help.  
38| 7| "Body Blows"| January 24, 2010 (2010-01-24)  
Bruce goes to a charity event for the [Boys & Girls Clubs of
America](/wiki/Boys_%26_Girls_Clubs_of_America "Boys & Girls Clubs of
America"). Kourtney, Kim, and Khloé were set to attend, but to his
disappointment, they do not show. He decides to hold a charity boxing event
for the [American Heart Association](/wiki/American_Heart_Association
"American Heart Association") and the people they fight turn out to be harmful
for them. When Kourtney babysits for a friend, she realizes she is not
prepared to have her own baby.  
39| 8| "Weekend From Hell"| January 31, 2010 (2010-01-31)  
Kourtney, Kim, and Khloé take a weekend trip to [Santa Barbara,
California](/wiki/Santa_Barbara,_California "Santa Barbara, California") to
have one final trip before the baby arrives, but Kim and Khloé leave Kourtney
out of everything and get drunk, upsetting Kourtney, who must abstain from
alcohol. Meanwhile, Kendall signs a modeling contract and Kylie gets jealous.  
40| 9| "I Want Your Sex"| February 14, 2010 (2010-02-14)  
Khloé makes a "[love tape](/wiki/Sex_tape "Sex tape")" for husband [Lamar
Odom](/wiki/Lamar_Odom "Lamar Odom") while he's on the road. Scott and Rob saw
the tape with Lamar which made Khloé embarrassed. Kourtney misses intimacy
with Scott, but is afraid to have sex because she does not want to hurt the
baby. She later takes a _Sex During Pregnancy_ class with Scott  
41| 10| "Blame It on The Alcohol"| February 15, 2010 (2010-02-15)  
During the one-hour special, the family travels to Las Vegas to celebrate
Kim’s birthday and attend an important business meeting. Kim bothered her
mother for not caring about her birthday, while Scott gets violently drunk. He
subsequently gets into a scuffle with his buddy, Rob Kardashian, who is also
drunk. Their unruly behavior sets the tone for the remainder of the night.
After Kris is able to break up the fight, she and Kourtney think that they are
able to subdue Scott and leave him in the hotel room to sober up. To
everyone’s surprise, Scott shows up to the dinner where his boss is present.
After using foul language, embarrassing himself and making everyone in
attendance uncomfortable, Scott gets in an argument with the waiter and shoves
a $100 bill in his mouth. The drama continues to unfold as Kourtney ends her
relationship with Scott because of his unforgivable actions.  
42| 11| "Delivering Baby Mason"| February 21, 2010 (2010-02-21)  
Scott returns to the house to apologize to Kris, but she refuses to give him
another chance. Worried about never seeing Kourtney again and possibly never
meeting his child, he frantically sends text and voice-mail messages until
Kourtney grants him a chance to explain himself in person. She finally
reconciles with him, and the whole family comes back together at her baby
shower. Kim faints from exhaustion and takes 2 weeks off, deciding that when
she does resume working, she will not take on so many responsibilities. After
Kourtney delivers her son, Mason Dash Disick, she announces that she will be
returning to Miami to hire new girls at the store, as only 2 are currently
working there. Khloé says she will go too although she would rather stay in
L.A. with Lamar; she compromises that she will not be there 24/7. Scott is
also going, to visit friends and open a nightclub. Kris is upset that Kourtney
and Scott will be taking Mason along, and Bruce tells Khloé her marriage is
more important than going to Miami.  
  
### Season 5
(2010)[[edit](/w/index.php?title=List_of_Keeping_Up_with_the_Kardashians_episodes&action=edit&section=7

43| 1| "Kim's House Party"| August 22, 2010 (2010-08-22)| 4.67[2]  
Kim buys a new house after her split with Reggie Bush. Kris thinks Kim is
acting too protective of her house, so she decides to throw a house party to
break Kim's house in much to Kim's chagrin. Meanwhile, Khloé and Kourtney
disagree on whether Scott is welcome in Khloé and Lamar's house after his
awful stunts from last season.  
44| 2| "Blind Date"| August 29, 2010 (2010-08-29)| 3.57[3]  
Kris sets up a blind date for Kim with an Armenian professional athlete.
Khloé's family pesters her for Laker-game tickets, which upsets her. When none
of them get tickets, they watch the game from the comfort of Khloé's home.  
45| 3| "The Missing Ring"| September 5, 2010 (2010-09-05)| 2.87[4]  
Khloé loses her 7-carat engagement ring and worries that Lamar will freak out,
but Rob finds it. Meanwhile, Bruce and Kris fight about the new garage: Bruce
feels Kris is taking over "his" only space in the house; she thinks he does
not appreciate all the work she has put into their home. The friction makes
Kendall and Kylie worry that their parents will divorce, but the parents
manage to resolve their petty issues and end up sleeping in the garage
together.  
46| 4| "My Bodyguard"| September 6, 2010 (2010-09-06)| 2.60[5]  
Kim develops a schoolgirl crush on her new Australian bodyguard despite the
fact that they both wanted to keep the relationship strictly professional. Kim
drinks a little too much and kisses her bodyguard goodnight. Later she tries
to fix the problem to make things less awkward around them. Meanwhile, Khloé
teaches Lamar how to swim.  
45| 5| "Botox and Cigarettes"| September 12, 2010 (2010-09-12)| 2.92[6]  
Kim receives another round of Botox injections after Kris says she has lines
around her eyes. Khloé goes along for moral support, and Kim suffers the side
effects of Botox: the skin around her eyes start turning purple. After this
incident, Kim swears that she will never get another injection. Meanwhile,
Kris is discovered smoking and Kourtney, Kendall, and Kylie try to get her to
quit; Kourtney plots to make Kris think that Kendall is smoking because of her
example. Kourtney buys nicotine-free cigarettes (honey and marshmallow) and
Kris decides to stop smoking.  
48| 6| "Kourt Goes A.W.O.L."| September 19, 2010 (2010-09-19)| 3.77[7]  
When nobody in Kourtney's family makes an effort to attend Scott's birthday
party in Las Vegas, Kourtney house-hunts in New York City. Her family soon
finds out, and Kris plots a belated surprise party for Scott. Meanwhile, Bruce
struggles with getting Kim's dog, Rocky, neutered.  
49| 7| "Match Made in Hell"| September 26, 2010 (2010-09-26)| 3.43[8]  
When Khloé constantly jokes that Rob is dating her best friend Malika, they
decide to pretend that they are. Meanwhile, Kris ponders managing the pop band
[BG5](/w/index.php?title=BG5&action=edit&redlink=1 "BG5 \(page does not
exist\)"), and after she decides, she wonders if she made the wrong decision.  
50| 8| "No Boys Allowed"| October 3, 2010 (2010-10-03)| 3.43[9]  
As Mason goes in for his 6-month check-up, Kourtney realizes she wants another
baby so her kids will be close in age like she and Kim were, but when she
obsesses about getting pregnant, Scott thinks she's taking all the fun out of
the process of trying. Meanwhile, Bruce has a hard time accepting that
12-year-old Kylie has male friends, and there's tension when she breaks the
rule about inviting a boy up to her room.
